      "span_text": "In this context, the good agreement of a 2.8 ka radiocarbon age in the active Balcanoona Creek terminal splay and the construction of a beach ridge at Lake Callabonna at ~2.7 ka [CITATION_1] implies that these events were short-lived, not enabling significant sediment delivery to the lake floor and limiting modifications to the playa marginal shoreline."
